  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Instalao de sawfish</title>



    <!--
    <para>

      First, adapt <application>sawfish</application> to build with GCC-10:
    </para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">patch -Np1 -i ../sawfish-&sawfish-version;-gcc10_fixes-1.patch</userinput></screen>
-->
<para>
      Instale <application>sawfish</application> executando os seguintes comandos:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr --with-pango  &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Esse pacote no vem com uma sute de teste.
    </para>

    <para>
      Agora, como o(a) usurio(a) <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem>:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This package creates six <filename>.desktop</filename> files in the
<filename class="directory">/usr/share/xsessions/</filename> directory.  All
but one are needed in a BLFS system, so prevent the extra files showing up
as options in a display manager.  As the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>rm -v /usr/share/xsessions/sawfish-*.desktop</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

